📽️A man armed with a rifle was shot by a quick-acting convenience store owner who pulled a shotgun out from behind the counter and opened fire during an attempted robbery in Southern California.⁠
⁠
The face-off was recorded by surveillance cameras at the convenience store around 2:45am. ⁠
⁠
Four suspects, their faces covered, pulled up to the business in a BMW SUV and walked inside the store with their rifles pointed, according to the Riverside County Sheriff’s Department

🔴 This is the horrifying moment a crane dropped a cylinder of chlorine gas, killing 13 in a Jordan port.

The force of the blast sent a truck rolling down the harbourside, while port workers were seen running for their lives.

At least 13 people died and 251 were injured in a chlorine gas leak from a storage tank at Jordan's Aqaba port, officials and state media reported on Monday

📹 Watch: 'We're going to need your boat', police commandeer family vessel in jet ski pursuit⁠
⁠
A family were taken by surprise on Sunday when two police officers approached them and asked to use their boat to help catch an alleged jet ski thief.⁠
⁠
The Volusia Sheriff's Office in Florida released footage of the exchange and subsequent police chase, showing the officers, with the owner's permission, taking to the water to find the suspect.⁠
⁠
The dramatic chase came to a head when the officers confronted the suspect, who was adrift on the water unable to get the jet ski started, telling him to swim to the boat. However, the man said he didn't know how. ⁠
⁠
🔗 Read more at the link in bio⁠
⁠
#usa #robbery #florida #police

latestPosts.caption:
Flesh-eating squirrels which hunt down and devour voles have been spotted for the first time in the wild.⁠
⁠
Until now, squirrels were thought to be primarily vegetarian, cramming their cheeks full of seeds and nuts, which they often bury in underground stores to get through the colder months.⁠
⁠
But biologists were amazed to see Californian ground squirrels chasing and killing voles in predatory behaviour never before recorded in the animals.⁠
⁠
🔗 Read more at the link in bio⁠
⁠
#squirrels #nature #voles #wildlife

latestPosts.caption:
🗣️ The family, including the Prince and Princess of Wales and their three children, have gathered at Sandringham today to celebrate Christmas together, following a particularly challenging year for its senior members.

The King’s words closely echo those of the Princess, who has spoken of the importance of kindness and helping others through difficulty since she finished her chemotherapy, including in an introduction for her Westminster Abbey carol service.

The King said: “All of us go through some form of suffering at some stage in our life, be it mental or physical.

“The degree to which we help one another – and draw support from each other, be we people of faith or of none – is a measure of our civilisation as nations.” 

🖇️ Click the link in @telegraph’s bio to read more 

#kingcharles #royals #princessofwales #christmas #health

🎄 The service, the Princess of Wales said, was a chance to “slow down and reflect on the deeper things that connect us all”.⁠
⁠
As hymns soared, fairy lights twinkled on fir trees sent by the King and the Wales children laid their messages of thanks on a Kindness Tree outside Westminster Abbey, few could fail to be moved by the spectacle or the sentiment.⁠
⁠
In a year that has been tough for the Royal family and countless others around the world, the Christmas carol service’s theme of love, kindness and empathy has rarely been needed more.⁠
⁠
